===Talking to Kit after opening the heavy chest===
* {{tcond|Immediately after unlocking the chest:}}
** '''Player:''' That's done! I'll let you check the contents out!
** '''Kit Breaker:''' That's great, thank you! I'll go and check it out right now!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{tcond|If the player speaks to Kit separately after unlocking the chest:}}
** '''Kit Breaker:''' Hello again, [player name]!
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|Talk about the beard.}}
*** {{tact|above}}
** {{topt|Talk about the equipment.}}
*** '''Player:''' I've unlocked the heavy chest! It's your things, though, so I didn't check the contents.
*** '''Kit Breaker:''' That's great, thank you! I'll go and check it out right now!
*** {{tact|continues}}
** {{topt|Nevermind.}}
*** {{tact|above}}
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Oh wow, there's my dad's old steel plate armour in there. He is not going to be happy when he realises that has gone missing.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' There's also a letter? Oh! It's a letter for me.
* '''Player:''' Are you going to read it?
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Should I? What if it's not meant to be read right now?
* '''Player:''' If it wasn't meant to be read I'm not sure what it's doing in there, addressed to you.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Okay, here goes.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Dearest Kit, I hope you'll find this eventually - I'm sneaking it in with the armour I'm packing for you.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Firstly, you might want to give all that old stuff a {{Colour|#0000ff|p}}olish. Your dad may not have used it in a while and I'm sure it'll be dusty.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Secondly, there should be a money pouch in amongst your stuff. You might need it on your adventures. I've also packed a few snacks. You'll need them after carrying those chests.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' You might think that we managed to keep your departure secret from your dad. I know you've been apprehensive of his reaction. I want to {{Colour|#0000ff|r}}eassure you.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' He loves you way more than he lets on. The other chest {{Colour|#0000ff|I}} gave you is actually from him, and the code to open it represents his feelings towards you.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' We'll miss you, but this is your chance to go and find yourself out in the world. You'll always be welcome home but I get the feeling it might be a while before you're back.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Never stop chasing your {{Colour|#0000ff|d}}reams. You've got a good heart and some... Decent armour to protect it with. Maybe look to replace it sooner rather than later.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Kit's a great name too. I can't wait to hear the stories of Kit Breaker doing something h{{Colour|#0000ff|e}}roic - just don't be too brave all of the time.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' We love you lots. Mum. P.S. The dog misses you too.
* '''Player:''' It sounds like your parents are actually really supportive.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' ... Yeah... 
* '''Kit Breaker:''' I should put on that armour.
* {{qact|Kit puts on the steel armour.}}
* '''Player:''' Looking sharp!
* '''Kit Breaker:''' I know, right? I never thought I'd see the day where I got to wear my dad's old armour! Growing up he always told me to stay away from it.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' I don't know how much damage I could have done to it, it's not particularly fragile. I assumed he didn't want me to become a knight, back then.
* '''Player:''' Maybe he was more worried about the damage the armour could do to you. That chestplate is pretty heavy after all.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' I'd never considered that, [player name]. I'll have to think about that later.
* {{tcond|If Kit has not yet received a haircut:}}
** {{tact|previous}}
* {{tcond|If Kit has already received a haircut:}}
** '''Kit Breaker:''' I'm really starting to look the part now! I just need some standard-issue weaponry and I'm good to go. Maybe it's time we unlocked the other chest.
** '''Kit Breaker:''' Yes. I think the letter from my mom held the key to opening it. Let me know if you want me to read it to you again.
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Kit Breaker after he has the haircut and armour===
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Hello again, [player name]!
