* {{tact|above}}

===Talking to Kit Breaker near the Squire===
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Hello! My name is Kit Breaker and I would like to enlist in the White Knights!
* '''Squire:''' Sure thing! First I have a bunch of forms to fill in with your details.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Oh! Ok!
* '''Squire:''' And here's a pamphlet about the joining process. For unproven recruits, you'll be a knight's squire like me for five years before becoming an initiate.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Five years!?
* '''Squire:''' Yes! I know it feels like it has been a lot longer than that for me, but it's not too bad.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Is there no way to accelerate the process?
* '''Squire:''' I wish I knew of one!
* '''Squire:''' Sir Amik can make people knights at his discretion, but that usually requires a truly heroic feat to have been performed. He's upstairs in the castle tower to the west of here.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' [player name], we should go and meet him directly. I'll head there right now, please join me there!
* {{qact|Kit leaves to meet Sir Amik.}}
* '''Player:''' Wait for me! Oh, he's already gone.
* {{mes|Objective: Meet Kit near Sir Amik, who is upstairs in the Falador Castle tower.|color=red}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Kit Breaker near Sir Amik Varze===
* '''Sir Amik Varze:''' I am the leader of the White Knights of Falador. Why do you seek my audience?
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Greetings, Sir! My name is Kit Breaker and I would like to enlist in the White Knights!
* '''Sir Amik Varze:''' A new recruit? Excellent! Please talk to the squire in the courtyard for the required paperwork!
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Would... Would it be possible to avoid the squire period and move straight to initiate, Sir?
* {{tcond|If the player has not completed [[Wanted!]]:}}
** '''Sir Amik Varze:''' That is an honour we reserve to those who have performed a heroic feat, such as defeating a dangerous criminal or performing a critical service for our order.
** '''Sir Amik Varze:''' Have you done anything that you think would qualify?
** {{tact|continue}}
* {{tcond|If the player has completed [[Wanted!]]:}}
** '''Sir Amik Varze:''' That is an honour we reserve to those who have performed a heroic feat. For instance, [player name] here defeated a dangerous criminal and as such became an honourary White Knight.
** '''Kit Breaker:''' You did? Why didn't you tell me earlier?
** '''Player:''' It's not the kind of thing I normally drop into a casual conversation. We all have different paths to achieve our goals, and you might have been discouraged seeing mine.
** '''Player:''' Being a White Knight was not my own end goal. I didn't want to detract from yours.
** '''Sir Amik Varze:''' Regardless, young man. Have you done anything that you think would qualify?
** {{tact|continue}}
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Well, I... Err... Have come a long way to be here, Sir and... Err... Oh, who am I kidding. I've never defeated a criminal. I couldn't even tell my dad to his face that I was leaving home.
* '''Sir Amik Varze:''' The path to being heroic takes many shapes. Keep looking and come back to me if you find it.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Thank you, Sir.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' I can't believe I genuinely thought I'd just waltz in here and get into the White Knights right away.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' I guess it's time for the walk of shame. I'll get back to my things and take this armour off. I'm not big enough to fill it.
* '''Player:''' Hey! Don't give up quite yet. I'm sure we can find a way.
* '''Kit Breaker:''' That's very kind of you, but I don't want to impose. Thanks for your help, [player name]. Despite my failure you've been a big help. I will see myself out, now.
* {{qact|Kit leaves.}}
* '''Player:''' Aaand he's gone. One sure thing, he is very good at running off. I should go and catch him up.
* {{mes|Objective: Meet Kit by his belongings, just north of Falador.|color=red}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Kit Breaker after Sir Amik Varze tells him to come back later===
* '''Kit Breaker:''' Hello, [player name]...
* '''Kit Breaker:''' I can't believe I genuinely thought I'd just waltz in here and get into the White Knights right away.
* {{tact|above}}

